posts.title: The carnal kingdom of Adam in each soul is being destroyed,  and it gets loud in the sixth trumpet sounding,  leading up to the kingdom change of the seventh trumpet sounding. The kingdom change takes place in each individual soul that puts faith in the life and reign of Jesus Christ
posts.content:
Revelation 10:3 And cried with a loud voice, as when a lion roareth: and when he had cried, seven thunders uttered their voices. 4 And when the seven thunders had uttered their voices, I was about to write: and I heard a voice from heaven saying unto me, Seal up those things which the seven thunders uttered, and write them not.

When The kingdom of Jesus Christ is bringing revealed in the individual soul in the sixth trumpet sounding it is loud, like seven thunders. This is the second woe on the carnal kingdom of man in each soul.

Revelation 8:13 Woe, woe, woe, to the inhabiters of the earth by reason of the other voices of the trumpet of the three angels, which are yet to sound!

The carnal kingdom of Adam in each soul is being destroyed, and it gets loud in the sixth trumpet sounding, leading up to the kingdom change of the seventh trumpet sounding. The kingdom change takes place in each individual soul that puts faith in the life and reign of Jesus Christ

Revelation 11:15 And the seventh angel sounded; and there were great voices in heaven, saying, The kingdoms of this world are become the kingdoms of our Lord, and of his Christ; and he shall reign for ever and ever.

Spiritual events in each soul are signified in symbols in the book of Revelation. The Christian soul is finding the kingdom that Jesus Christ brings, in the spiritual new creation, brought on by the seven trumpets sounding. This is the work of the Holy Spirit in each Christian.
